# Initial query

The `--query` flag should seed the interactive filter before the picker draws.

    :bins jj cat tmux

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'cat', and 'tmux' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s beta "printf 'beta target'; cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s gamma "printf 'gamma target'; cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh --query gam" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 80 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

The prompt should contain the seeded query, and the list should be filtered to
matching sessions.

    :snap

```terminal
session: gam
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag
▌⬤ gamma                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────






```

